headline: Block Pares Gains as Solid Earnings Fail to Wow Investors
summary: Shares of  Block  the parent of Square and Cash App, popped after the company reported second-quarter results after the closing bell Thursday.  At first glance, there was a lot to love about Block’s second-quarter print.  Gross profit, a key performance indicator, rose 14% to $2.54 billion in the quarter, beating the $2.46 billion consensus estimate among analysts polled by FactSet.
